Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}(peeled). Thinly slice one half; finely dice remaining. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and thinly sliced). Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Drain @corn{13.4%oz}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add sliced onion and poblano and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and tender, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add half the corn (all for 4 servings) and cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer veggies to a #large bowl{}; cover to keep warm.

Pat @ranch steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Set aside on a #cutting board{} to rest.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add diced onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @chipotle powder{1/8%tsp} (we sent more) and cook until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}. Stir in @water{1/4%cup} (⅓ cup for 4 servings) and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Let simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in @sour cream{2%tbsp}.

> TIP: If you like things spicy, add more chipotle powder to taste.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Add potatoes and a squeeze of lime juice to bowl with veggies; toss to combine, then divide between plates. Top veggies with steak and drizzle steak with sauce. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.